reviews.text: Good location but lack of trains with one every few hours on week days and more trains on weekends. Facilities lacking the departure board doesn't work

This station looks like a make shift station lol.Lack of staff,no cafe,no toilets,no lifts,departure boards not working etc.All the basic amenities you would expect in a station,however the station is very closely located to the new forest wildlife park which has stunning views and wildlife;hence the very generous three stars.

Fairly small. I like the station because it is fancy in it's own way. You have to look closely to see it, though. It is small, which equals easy to navigate. Some might say that they don't like a place because it is small, but I like it for the reason I just mentioned, easy to navigate. Try this station. You might like it!

Please note the train station is 3 miles from Beaulieu village and the motor museum.There is a bus stop.Please plan your visit better than i did.Great walks in the area.Welcome to wide open spaces.Great area if you want to explore by bike.May i explain i was looking at a camping website and it suggested Beaulieu station was a short walk away.Not so.
A railway station on the South Western Main Line. Steam trains pass through regularly and often stop here for water.
